=======================================================
=  Centreon Command Line API
=======================================================

In order to install Centreon Command line API Module, follow the 
next step :

1. Unzip files 

#> tar -xzf centreon-clapi-1.0.tar.gz

2. Copy file into centreon modules directory

In the example, /usr/local/centreon is centreon install path

#> cp -Rf ./centreon-clapi /usr/local/centreon/www/modules/

3. Apply right on files 

#> dos2unix /usr/local/centreon/www/modules/centreon-clapi/core/centreon
#> chmod +x /usr/local/centreon/www/modules/centreon-clapi/core/centreon

Now you can use Centreon Common Line API.

Example :

#> cd /usr/local/centreon/www/modules/centreon-clapi/core/
#> ./centreon -u jmathis -p centreon -a applycfg -v 1
#> ./centreon -u jmathis -p centreon -a pollerlist

